I '''Patricia Highsmith''' (Enero 19, 1921 – Febrero 4, 1995) metung yang Americanang nobelista ampong talasulat makuyad a salita (''short story writer'') a pikabaluan dili kareng kayang [[psychological thrillers]], nung nu deng maigit adwang dusena la reng megawang pelikula. Ing mumuna nang nobela, ing ''[[Strangers on a Train (nobela)|Strangers on a Train]]'', dakal neng ukdu o besis mibage ne king entabladu ampong sine, at karapatdapat banggitan a metung ya kareti ing kang [[Alfred Hitchcock]] anyang 1951. Bukud kareng kayang pupurian dang serie tungkul king makamate taung i [[Tom Ripley]], dakal ya sinulat a [[makuyad a salita]], she wrote many [[(''short story''), a maralas makapangilabut, |short stories]], often (''macabre''), satirika, o maralas, tatagkilan ning kapitutulan tungkul king kamatayan (''black humor''). Lipat ning sinulat ya partikular king uring pikudtang krimen (''crime fiction''), pupurian do reng kayang libru deng miayaliwang talasulat ampong kritiku uli kanung artistiku la ampong malalam, a malyari lang itulid king king tatalukyan o a literatura o panyulat (mainstream literature''). Nga nang [[Michael Dirda]], "Parangalan de deng Europeo antimong sikolohikal a nobelista, a kayabe king tradisyong [[existentialist]], nung nu ding pekakatawan deng kayang paboritung talasulat, partikular di [[Fyodor Dostoevsky|Dostoevsky]], [[Joseph Conrad|Conrad]], [[Franz Kafka|Kafka]], [[André Gide|Gide]], ampong [[Albert Camus|Camus]]." ("Europeans honored her as a psychological novelist, part of an [[existentialist]] tradition represented by her own favorite writers, in particular [[Fyodor Dostoevsky|Dostoevsky]], [[Joseph Conrad|Conrad]], [[Franz Kafka|Kafka]], [[André Gide|Gide]], and [[Albert Camus|Camus]].")<ref>[http://www.nybooks.com/articles/22797 "This Woman Is Dangerous"] ''The New York Review of Books''. July 2, 2009. Accessed November 15, 2009.</ref>

